             Renovalia Energy SA, the Spanish
solar and wind power producer that in May postponed an initial
public offering, said it plans a 200-million euro ($258 million)
wind park in Canadaâ€™s Alberta province.  
 The facility will have an electricity generating capacity
of 120 megawatts, and construction will begin the first quarter
of 2011, Renovalia said today in an e-mailed statement.  
